 <title>The Thread class</title>
 <titleabbrev>Thread</titleabbrev>
  
 <partintro>

<!-- {{{ Thread intro -->
  <section xml:id="pht.thread.intro">
   &reftitle.intro;
   <para>
    The <classname>Thread</classname> class abstracts away a native thread. It
    has an internal task queue, where the methods
    <methodname>Thread::addClassTask</methodname>,
    <methodname>Thread::addFunctionTask</methodname>, and
    <methodname>Thread::addFileTask</methodname> push new tasks onto this
    queue. Invoking the <methodname>Thread::start</methodname> method will
    cause the new thread to be spawned, where it will then begin working
    through the task queue. A thread may be reused for any number of tasks.
   </para>
  </section>
